Matlab has been configured to use only one computational thread.
You can increase the number of computational threads by issuing the 
command "unalias matlab" before starting matlab and using the 
maxNumCompThreads function. If you do that, please request additional
processors when you submit your job. For example, if you request 4 
computational threads, you should have:
#PBS -l nodes=1:ppn=4 in your job file.
